Rating: 4
I made this recipe so easily with some help from Trader Joe. I sauteed a flank steak in a cast iron pan for about 5 minutes, removed it and threw in a few handfuls of TJ frozen roasted corn, while cooking a bag of prewashed haricots verts in the microwave. Then added them to the pan with the corn, then added some jarred TJ pesto, Meanwhile sliced up the steak and finding it undercooked threw the slices back in the pan, where the residual heat finished them perfectly. Served it right from the cast iron fry pan.

